            </button>
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">Dota2Stats</a>
          </div>
          <div class="navbar-collapse collapse">
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
              <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
              <li><a href="/player/">Most Recent Matches</a></li>

              <li class="dropdown">
              <a id="drop1" href="#" role="button" class="dropdown-toggle" data-toggle="dropdown">Favorite Players <b class="caret"></b></a>
              <ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu" aria-labelledby="drop1">
                <li role="presentation"><a role ="menuitem" tabindex="-1" href="/player/64931387">Ganex</a></li>
                <li role="presentation"><a role ="menuitem" tabindex="-1" href="/player/32397469">Binderpaper</a></li>
                <li role="presentation"><a role ="menuitem" tabindex="-1" href="/player/884457">Johnnytsunami</a></li>
                <li role="presentation"><a role ="menuitem" tabindex="-1" href="/player/36520072">BRKNCAPSLOCKKEY</a></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav navbar-right">
              <li class="dropdown pull-right">
        <a class="dropdown-toggle" id="about" data-toggle="dropdown" href="#">About <b class="caret"></b></a>

        <ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu" aria-labelledby="about" id="toggleList">
          <div class="about">
            Dota2Stats is a match statistics aggregator for <a href="http://store.steampowered.com/app/570/">Dota2</a> the videogame.
            You can search for a particular player ID and find the most recent 
            games played by that person. Additionally, each match can be clicked on
            to get more detailed information on the match played including kills,
            gold collected and hero levels.
            <br><br>
            <strong>Notes</strong>
            <ul>
              <li>For convenience check out the Favorite Players dropdown for some players to click on if you don't have a player ID ready</li>
            
              <li>Invalid player ID's will raise a 404</li>

              <li>An API key is already provided in `config/application.rb`.</li>
              <li>The Steam API limits one API call per second.Do not request more than one page per second.</li>

            </ul>
          </div>
        </ul>

      </li>
            </ul>
